wiki.content: "My Future" is a song recorded by American singer-songwriter Billie Eilish, released on July 30, 2020, by Darkroom and Interscope Records. It was the first single to be released from Happier Than Ever, Billie's second studio album, exactly a year prior. The singer, known for her distinctive style, co-wrote the song with her brother Finneas, who not only contributed to the songwriting but also handled the production, showcasing the siblings' collaborative prowess. An R&B and ambient ballad with influences of soul and jazz, "My Future" represents a departure from Billie Eilish's earlier works, demonstrating her evolving musical palette. The incorporation of these diverse elements contributes to the song's rich and textured sound. Lyrically, the song serves as an introspective exploration, offering an ode to self-love and personal power. Billie Eilish's candid and authentic approach to songwriting shines through, connecting with listeners on a personal level. The poignant lyrics, combined with Eilish's emotive delivery, make "My Future" a compelling and resonant piece. The release of "My Future" not only marked a significant moment in Billie Eilish's career but also heightened anticipation for the subsequent release of "Happier Than Ever." The success of the single solidified Billie Eilish's position as a leading figure in the contemporary music landscape. Read more on Last.fm.
